SIMPLE: mannequin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mannequin
<hw>mannequin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a woman who wears
clothes to display fashions; a fashion model.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fashion model, model.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A three-dimensional model of a person, used to
display clothes, especially in retail stores and in window displays; a
dummy.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> manikin, mannikin, manakin.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A model of a human form used by tailors to help make
clothing of the proper shape.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manner</ent>⟦br⟧
